ation=[[Juneau]]|publisher=Alaska Municipal League/[[Alaska Department of Commerce, Community and Economic Development|Alaska Department of Community and Regional Affairs]]|date=January 1996|page=129}}</ref>\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|area_footnotes           = <ref name=\"CenPopGazetteer2016\">{{cite web|title=2018 U.S. Gazetteer Files|url=https://www2.census.gov/geo/docs/maps-data/data/gazetteer/2018_Gazetteer/2018_gaz_place_02.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=Jul 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_sq_mi         = 51.57\n|area_land_sq_mi          = 44.60\n|area_water_sq_mi         = 6.96\n\n<!-- Population -->\n|population_as_of         = [[2010 United States Census|2010]]\n|population_footnotes     = \n|population_total         = 507\n|population_density_km2   = 4.91\n|pop_est_as_of = 2018\n|pop_est_footnotes = <ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\"/>\n|population_est = 567\n|population_density_sq_mi = 12.71\n<!-- auto -->\n<!--postal codes & others -->\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code              = 99658\n|area_code                = [[Area code 907|907]]\n|area_code_type           = [[North American Numbering Plan|Area code]]\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 02-66140\n|blank1_name              = \n|blank1_info              = \n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n|unit_pref = Imperial\n|area_total_km2 = 133.56\n|area_land_km2 = 115.53\n|area_water_km2 = 18.03\n}}\n\n'''St. Mary's''' ({{lang-esu|Negeqliq}}) is a city in [[Kusilvak Census Area, Alaska]], United States. The adjacent village of '''Andreafsky''' (historically known as '''Clear River''') joined with St. Mary's in 1980.<ref>{{cite web|title=The History of Andreafsky|url=http://explorenorth.com/library/communities/alaska/bl-Andreafsky.htm|website=ExploreNorth|accessdate=22 December 2016}}</ref> At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] the population was 507, up from 500 in 2000. By 2018, the population was estimated to be 567.\n\nWithin Saint Mary's there are two [[List of Alaska Native tribal entities|federally-recognized tribes]] the ''Algaaciq Tribal Government'' and the ''Yuupiit of Andreafsky''.<ref>Nicole Herman-Mercer, 2010. [https://archive.org/details/HermanMercerNicole Indigenous environmental knowledge: past cases and future prospects]</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nSt. Mary's is located at {{coord|62|2|43|N|163|13|7|W|region:US_type:city}} (62.045305, -163.218629).<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/time-series/geo/gazetteer-files.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2011-04-23|date=2011-02-12|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of {{convert|50.2|sqmi|km2}}, of which, {{convert|44.0|sqmi|km2}} of it is land and {{convert|6.3|sqmi|km2}} of it (12.47%) is water.\n\n===Climate===\n{{Weather box\n| collapsed =\n| location = St. Mary's, Alaska\n| single line = Y\n| Jan record high F = 46 \n| Feb record high F = 41 \n| Mar record high F = 43 \n| Apr record high F = 60 \n| May record high F = 78 \n| Jun record high F = 80 \n| Jul record high F = 84 \n| Aug record high F = 95\n| Sep record high F = 73 \n| Oct record high F = 57 \n| Nov record high F = 43 \n| Dec record high F = 41 \n|year record high F = \n| Jan high F = 14.4\n| Feb high F = 15.2\n| Mar high F = 23.9\n| Apr high F = 32.4\n| May high F = 51.7\n| Jun high F = 59.7\n| Jul high F = 63.7\n| Aug high F = 62.0\n| Sep high F = 53.5\n| Oct high F = 36.5\n| Nov high F = 23.1\n| Dec high F = 13.6\n|year high F = \n|Jan mean F = 8.3\n|Feb mean F = 7.3\n|Mar mean F = 15.2\n|Apr mean F = 25.0\n|May mean F = 42.4\n|Jun mean F = 50.8\n|Jul mean F = 55.3\n|Aug mean F = 53.4\n|Sep mean F = 44.8\n|Oct mean F = 30.1\n|Nov mean F = 16.9\n|Dec mean F = 6.4\n|year mean F = \n| Jan low F = 2.2\n| Feb low F = -0.7\n| Mar low F = 6.4\n| Apr low F = 17.6\n| May low F = 33.1\n| Jun low F = 41.8\n| Jul low F = 46.9\n| Aug low F = 44.8\n| Sep low F = 36.0\n| Oct low F = 23.6\n| Nov low F = 10.6\n| Dec low F = -0.8\n|year low F = \n| Jan record low F = \u221244\n| Feb record low F = \u221242\n| Mar record low F = \u221240\n| Apr record low F = \u221223\n| May record low F = 2\n| Jun record low F = 26\n| Jul record low F = 30\n| Aug record low F = 29\n| Sep record low F = 15\n| Oct record low F = -13\n| Nov record low F = \u221229\n| Dec record low F = \u221241\n|year record low F = \n|precipitation colour =  \n| Jan precipitation inch = 1.02\n| Feb precipitation inch = 0.72\n| Mar precipitation inch = 0.80\n| Apr precipitation inch = 0.78\n| May precipitation inch = 0.82\n| Jun precipitation inch = 2.08\n| Jul precipitation inch = 2.69\n| Aug precipitation inch = 3.15\n| Sep precipitation inch = 2.32\n| Oct precipitation inch = 1.59\n| Nov precipitation inch = 1.60\n| Dec precipitation inch = 1.49\n|year precipitation inch = \n|Jan snow inch = 9.5\n|Feb snow inch = 5.0\n|Mar snow inch = 8.0\n|Apr snow inch = 5.4\n|May snow inch = 1.1\n|Jun snow inch = 0.8\n|Jul snow inch = 0.0\n|Aug snow inch = 0.0\n|Sep snow inch = 0.8\n|Oct snow inch = 5.8\n|Nov snow inch = 15.0\n|Dec snow inch = 16.4\n|year snow inch = \n|source 1 = WRCC <ref name=\"climate\">[http://wrcc.dri.edu/cgi-bin/cliMAIN.pl?ak8105 St Mary's, Alaska - Period of Record : 7/1/1967 to 5/31/2000] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170509023911/http://www.wrcc.dri.edu/cgi-bin/cliMAIN.pl?ak8105 |date=2017-05-09 }}. Retrieved November 10, 2019.</ref>\n|date=October 2019}}\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1960= 225\n|1970= 384\n|1980= 382\n|1990= 441\n|2000= 500\n|2010= 507\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=567\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=June 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\nSaint Mary's first appeared on the 1960 U.S. Census as an unincorporated village. It was formally incorporated in 1967.\n\n[[File:St Marys AK.JPG|thumb|left|Sunrise over St. Mary's.]]\nAs of the census<ref name=\"GR2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 500 people, 137 households, and 90 families residing in the city.  The population density was 11.4 people per square mile (4.4/km\u00b2).  There were 186 housing units at an average density of 4.2 per square&nbsp;mile (1.6/km\u00b2).  The racial makeup of the city was 11.20% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 87.20% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]]. 0.40% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.\n\nThere were 137 households out of which 45.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 40.9% were married couples living together, 17.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 34.3% were non-families. 28.5% of all households were made up of individuals and 2.2% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 3.58 and the average family size was 4.60.\n\nIn the city, the age distribution of the population shows 39.6% under the age of 18, 8.6% from 18 to 24, 30.4% from 25 to 44, 15.0% from 45 to 64, and 6.4% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 26 years. For every 100 females, there were 122.2 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 111.2 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in the city was $39,375, and the median income for a family was $31,875. Males had a median income of $35,313 versus $22,250 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $15,837.  About 21.5% of families and 20.4% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 28.2% of those under age 18 and 10.3% of those age 65 or over.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Alaska}}\n*[[Andreafsky Wilderness]]\n*[[Andreafsky River]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.commerce.alaska.gov/dcra/DCRAExternal/community/Details/52b44e86-bc0c-4365-95e8-b7ce946dc37c Andreafsky] and [https://www.commerce.alaska.gov/dcra/DCRAExternal/community/Details/1ad37cec-4f93-4135-ac2f-03faf342a1b7 Saint Mary's] at the Community Database Online from the [[Alaska Department of Commerce, Community and Economic Development|Alaska Division of Community and Regional Affairs]]\n* Maps from the [[Alaska Department of Labor and Workforce Development]]: [http://labor.alaska.gov/research/alari/images/maps/6_26_273map.pdf 2000], [http://labor.alaska.gov/research/census/maps/place/2014/66140.pdf 2010]\n\n{{Kusilvak Census Area, Alaska}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Saint Marys, Alaska}}\n[[Category:Cities in Alaska]]\n[[Category:Cities in Kusilvak Census Area, Alaska]]\n[[Category:Road-inaccessible communities of Alaska]]\n[[Category:Yukon River]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Saint Mary's\n|native_name              = Negeqliq\n|settlement_type          = [[City (Alaska)|City]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    = <!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = \n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = \n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               = <!-- Maps -->\n|coordinates              = {{coord|62|2|43|N|163|13|7|W|region:US_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n|pushpin_map            = Alaska\n|pushpin_label_position = left <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location within the state of Alaska\n