r files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of {{convert|50.2|sqmi|km2}}, of which, {{convert|44.0|sqmi|km2}} of it is land and {{convert|6.3|sqmi|km2}} of it (12.47%) is water.\n\n===Climate===\n{{Weather box\n| collapsed =\n| location = St. Mary's, Alaska\n| single line = Y\n| Jan record high F = 46 \n| Feb record high F = 41 \n| Mar record high F = 43 \n| Apr record high F = 60 \n| May record high F = 78 \n| Jun record high F = 80 \n| Jul record high F = 84 \n| Aug record high F = 95\n| Sep record high F = 73 \n| Oct record high F = 57 \n| Nov record high F = 43 \n| Dec record high F = 41 \n|year record high F = \n| Jan high F = 14.4\n| Feb high F = 15.2\n| Mar high F = 23.9\n| Apr high F = 32.4\n| May high F = 51.7\n| Jun high F = 59.7\n| Jul high F = 63.7\n| Aug high F = 62.0\n| Sep high F = 53.5\n| Oct high F = 36.5\n| Nov high F = 23.1\n| Dec high F = 13.6\n|year high F = \n|Jan mean F = 8.3\n|Feb mean F = 7.3\n|Mar mean F = 15.2\n|Apr mean F = 25.0\n|May mean F = 42.4\n|Jun mean F = 50.8\n|Jul mean F = 55.3\n|Aug mean F = 53.4\n|Sep mean F = 44.8\n|Oct mean F = 30.1\n|Nov mean F = 16.9\n|Dec mean F = 6.4\n|year mean F = \n| Jan low F = 2.2\n| Feb low F = -0.7\n| Mar low F = 6.4\n| Apr low F = 17.6\n| May low F = 33.1\n| Jun low F = 41.8\n| Jul low F = 46.9\n| Aug low F = 44.8\n| Sep low F = 36.0\n| Oct low F = 23.6\n| Nov low F = 10.6\n| Dec low F = -0.8\n|year low F = \n| Jan record low F = \u221244\n| Feb record low F = \u221242\n| Mar record low F = \u221240\n| Apr record low F = \u221223\n| May record low F = 2\n| Jun record low F = 26\n| Jul record low F = 30\n| Aug record low F = 29\n| Sep record low F = 15\n| Oct record low F = -13\n| Nov record low F = \u221229\n| Dec record low F = \u221241\n|year record low F = \n|precipitation colour =  \n| Jan precipitation inch = 1.02\n| Feb precipitation inch = 0.72\n| Mar precipitation inch = 0.80\n| Apr precipitation inch = 0.78\n| May p